tao the martial art of drumming events at stanford tao the martial art of drumming facebook twitter email print add to calendar veritable rock stars of taiko japanese for drum the 20 virtuoso members of tao make breathtaking use of their disciplined athletic conditioning imagine a 12 mile run followed by four hours of non stop drumming all in a day's work for tao at its rural compound on the island of kyushu but the secret ingredient that has earned tao its reputation as one of the world's top taiko companies is its dynamic modern take on traditional japanese drumming which includes anime martial arts newly composed music and blazing choreography generously supported by dr morton grosser and adam grosser and sher amos grosser when tuesday february 14 2012 8 00 pm where memorial auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags arts performance music sponsor stanford lively arts contact 650 725 arts 2787 livelyarts stanford edu admission reserved seating $28 40 48 premium $68 permalink http events stanford edu events 285 28523 more info last modified february 2 2012
